        public Command(CommandValue c,
               java.lang.String summary,

               java.lang.String estimate,
               java.lang.String developerId,
               Rejection reason)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor for Command class. A Command encapsulates the seven possible user actions. A Command is created by a message from the GUI and is issued down through RequirementTrackerModel, RequirementsList, Requirement, and RequirementState. This constructor handles precondition checks for the parameters associated with each command.
        Parameters:
        c - the CommandValue enumeration for this Command
        summary - the summary for this Command
        acceptanceTestId - the acceptanceTestId for this Command
        priority - the priority for this Command
        estimate - the estimate for this Command
        developerId - the developerId for this Command
        reason - the Rejection enumeration for this Command
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a required parameter for the Command is invalid
